implementationPlan.description:
Auto-announce new workers to #general in claimNextTask.ts.

In `packages/moe-daemon/src/tools/claimNextTask.ts`:

1. After `state.createWorker()` (line 131, inside the `if (!existingWorker)` branch), auto-announce to #general using `state.postToGeneral()`:
```typescript
try {
  const roleLabel = statuses.includes('PLANNING') ? 'architect'
    : statuses.includes('REVIEW') ? 'qa' : 'worker';
  await state.postToGeneral(`${params.workerId} is online (${roleLabel})`);
} catch { /* never block claim */ }
```

2. After task channel system message (line 148), auto-set chatCursors for the task channel:
```typescript
if (taskChannel && params.workerId) {
  try {
    const worker = state.getWorker(params.workerId);
    if (worker) {
      const cursors = { ...(worker.chatCursors || {}) };
      if (!cursors[taskChannel.id]) {
        cursors[taskChannel.id] = '';
        await state.updateWorker(params.workerId, { chatCursors: cursors });
      }
    }
  } catch { /* never block tool */ }
}
```

3. Before return, find generalChannelId and add it to the response object alongside `channelId`:
```typescript
let generalChannelId: string | null = null;
for (const ch of state.channels.values()) {
  if (ch.type === 'general' || ch.name === 'general') { generalChannelId = ch.id; break; }
}
```

Error handling: All additions wrapped in try/catch to never block the core claim operation.
